<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-03-05T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-03-05T19:00:00-05:00" n="914" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d914">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.001W69/2.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-03-05T19:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 5, 1913—7 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>78. Your March 4, conveying a message to the President from General Felix
                            Díaz. The President desires you to say orally to General Díaz that his
                            message is highly appreciated, that his good wishes are reciprocated,
                            and that he hopes the restoration of peace and prosperity throughout
                            Mexico will soon be brought about.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>